text: Nathan Warren Harter (November 15, 1884 – January 9, 1952) was an American football coach and mathematics professor. He served as the head football coach at Thiel College in Greenville, Pennsylvania from 1911 to 1912. Harter was a 1909 graduate of Wittenberg College. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1884 births Category:1952 deaths Category:Thiel Tomcats football coaches Category:Wittenberg University alumni Category:People from Medina, Ohio
